Business history[edit]
Taghleef Industries Inc[edit]
Khoury founded Taghleef Industries Inc (formerly Applied Extrusion Technologies Inc.) and served as the Chairman from October 1986 to March 2005. He also served as President from August 1988 to November 1992 and as Chief Executive Officer from October 2002 to March 2005.[4]
B/E Aerospace[edit]
Amin Khoury co-founded B/E Aerospace Inc (NASDAQ: BEAV) in July 1987. An investment group led by Khoury purchased Bach Engineering, a company that manufactured passenger control units for airline seats, in 1987. In 1989, the group purchased EECO Avionics, their primary competitor. This formed B/E Avionics and the company went public in 1990. The company changed its name to B/E Aerospace in 1992.[5] Khoury has been a Director at B/E since founding it in 1987. He served as the Chief Executive Officer from July 1987 to April 1996, then again from December 2005 to December 2014. He is the Executive Chairman of the Board, serving in that capacity since December 2014.[4]
Synthes[edit]
Between 1986 and April 2012, Amin Khoury served non-executive Director at Synthes Inc., a medical device manufacturer. He was also a director at Johnson & Johnson. [4]
Brooks Automation[edit]
Between July 1994 to May 2006, Khoury was the Lead Independent Director at Brooks Automation.[4]
Advanced Thermal Sciences[edit]
Amin Khoury co-founded co-founded Advanced Thermal Sciences in July 2000 and served as the chief executive officer.[6] He now serves as chairman and a director.[4]
KLX Inc.[edit]
Khoury is the CEO and Chairman of KLX Inc, a provider of aerospace fasteners, consumables, and logistics services. [7][4]
Other business[edit]
Khoury is an advisor at D2K Equity Partners.[8][4]
Philanthropy and social responsibility[edit]
Khoury is involved with numerous charitable organizations. He was a Trustee of the Scripps Research Institute from May 2008[9][4] until July 2014.[7] He also serves on the board of directors of the Raymond F. Kravis Center for the Performing Arts and is the chair of the center's Investment Committee.[10][9]
Khoury and his wife established the Amin and Julie Khoury Endowed Scholarship at Northeastern University.[1]
Education and honors[edit]
Amin Khoury holds bachelor's and master's degrees in chemistry from Northeastern University. He graduated summa cum laude from Northeastern with a master's degree in business administration (MBA). He was also awarded the university's prestigious Medallion Achievement Award.[9][4]
In addition to his academic education, Khoury holds a Masters Professional Director Certification from the American College of Corporate Directors and an Advanced Director Certification from the Corporate Directors Group.[4]
